      • ACTION_AUTHORIZE_SEED_ACCESS

        public static final String ACTION_AUTHORIZE_SEED_ACCESS
        Intent action to request that a new seed be authorized for usage by the calling app. The Intent should also contain an EXTRA_PURPOSE extra, specifying the purpose for which the seed should be authorized.

        On Activity.RESULT_OK, the resulting Intent will contain an EXTRA_AUTH_TOKEN extra with the authorization token for the newly authorized seed.

        If the Activity is cancelled for any reason, Activity.RESULT_CANCELED will be returned. If the specified purpose is not one of the PURPOSE_* values, RESULT_INVALID_PURPOSE will be returned. If there are no seeds available to be authorized with the specified purpose, RESULT_NO_AVAILABLE_SEEDS will be returned. If the user failed to authorize the transaction, RESULT_AUTHENTICATION_FAILED will be returned.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ACTION_SIGN_TRANSACTION

        public static final String ACTION_SIGN_TRANSACTION
        Intent action to request that a set of transactions be signed. The Intent should contain an EXTRA_SIGNING_REQUEST extra SigningRequests, one per transaction to be signed. Each SigningRequest may contain multiple requested signature BIP derivation paths. These derivation paths should be Uris with a scheme of either BIP32_URI_SCHEME or BIP44_URI_SCHEME. The Intent should also contain an EXTRA_AUTH_TOKEN extra specifying the authorized seed with which to sign.

        On Activity.RESULT_OK, the resulting Intent will contain an EXTRA_SIGNING_RESPONSE extra with SigningResponses, one per SigningRequest. Each SigningResponse contains the requested signatures.

        If the Activity is cancelled for any reason, Activity.RESULT_CANCELED will be returned. If the specified auth token is not valid, RESULT_INVALID_AUTH_TOKEN will be returned. If any transaction is not valid for signing with this auth token, RESULT_INVALID_TRANSACTION will be returned. If any requested signature derivation path is not a valid BIP32 or BIP44 derivation path Uri, RESULT_INVALID_DERIVATION_PATH will be returned. If the user failed to authorize signing the set of transactions, RESULT_AUTHENTICATION_FAILED will be returned. If the number of SigningRequests or the number of BIP derivation paths in a SigningRequest is more than the quantity supported by the Seed Vault implementation, RESULT_IMPLEMENTATION_LIMIT_EXCEEDED will be returned.

        See Also:
        Bip32DerivationPath, Bip44DerivationPath, Constant Field Values

      • ACTION_GET_PUBLIC_KEY

        public static final String ACTION_GET_PUBLIC_KEY
        Intent action to request the public key for a set of accounts. The Intent should contain an EXTRA_DERIVATION_PATH extra with account BIP derivation path URIs, each with a scheme of either BIP32_URI_SCHEME or BIP44_URI_SCHEME. The Intent should also contain an EXTRA_AUTH_TOKEN extra specifying the authorized seed from which to derive the account public keys. If all of these accounts are present in ACCOUNTS_TABLE, the public keys will be returned without requiring user authentication.

        On Activity.RESULT_OK, the resulting Intent will contain an EXTRA_PUBLIC_KEY extra with PublicKeyResponses, one per BIP derivation path URI.

        If the Activity is cancelled for any reason, Activity.RESULT_CANCELED will be returned. If any requested account derivation path is not a valid BIP32 or BIP44 derivation path Uri, RESULT_INVALID_DERIVATION_PATH will be returned. If the specified auth token is not valid, RESULT_INVALID_AUTH_TOKEN will be returned. If the user failed to authorize the transaction, RESULT_AUTHENTICATION_FAILED will be returned. If the number of account BIP derivation path URIs is more than the quantity supported by the Seed Vault implementation, RESULT_IMPLEMENTATION_LIMIT_EXCEEDED will be returned.

        See Also:
        Bip32DerivationPath, Bip44DerivationPath, Constant Field Values

      • RESULT_NO_AVAILABLE_SEEDS

        public static final int RESULT_NO_AVAILABLE_SEEDS
        There are no seeds available to authorize in response to ACTION_AUTHORIZE_SEED_ACCESS for the requested purpose. This may be due to either there being no seeds available for that purpose, or that the app has already authorized all available seeds for that purpose. Callers can check the AUTHORIZED_SEEDS_TABLE to disambiguate between these two cases.
